The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has condemned the pipelineÂ explosion in Abule Ado and Festac Town areas of Lagos on Sunday.
Bola Tinubu in a statement by Tunde Rahman, expressed his sympathy for the families and relations of those who lost their lives in the unfortunate occurrence.
Tinubu advocated that all those who had a hand in the unfortunate incident, including those who acted in ways to put lives at risk and hard-earned possessions in jeopardy, must be punished no matter how highly placed.
The explosion caused the death of some persons while many others suffered varying degrees of injuries. The figure of deaths is not certain yet, however, rescue operations are still going on. Houses And vehicles were also burnt in the inferno.

			
